		<h2>FULL DEGREE STUDY</h2><p>International students make up about 12% of the students across the School, with programmes like our internationally acclaimed MFA having about 50% international students.</p><h2>UNDERGRADUATE</h2><p>Most undergraduate courses at the GSA take place over 4 years. International students would normally apply to year 1 of the programmes, although in exceptional circumstances, students with the right backgrounds can be admitted to the second year. </p><p>The following courses are available:</p><p><b>Mackintosh School of Architecture: </b><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=200" target="new window"><u>BArch</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=200" target="new window"><u>BArch (Hons)</u></a></p><p><b>School of Design</b><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=113" target="new window"><u>BA (Hons) Design Ceramics</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=843" target="new window"><u>BA (Hons) Design Ceramic (part-time)</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=121" target="new window"><u>BA (Hons) Design Interior Design</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=156" target="new window"><u>BA (Hons) Design Silversmithing and Jewellery</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=165" target="new window"><u>BA (Hons) Design Textiles</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=172" target="new window"><u>BA (Hons) Design Visual Communication</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=130" target="new window"><u>BDes/MEDes in Product Design</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=138" target="new window"><u>BEng/MEng in Product Design Engineering </u></a>(taught jointly with the University of Glasgow)</p><p><b>School of Fine Art</b><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=6" target="new window"><u>BA (Hons) Fine Art Painting and Printmaking</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=8" target="new window"><u>BA (Hons) Fine Art Photography</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=7" target="new window"><u>BA (Hons) Fine Art Evironmental Art and Sculpture</u></a></p><h2>UCAS</h2><p>Undergraduate applications are made through the Universities and Colleges Admissions Service (UCAS). Applications are made on line at:  <a href="http://www.ucas.com" target="new window"><u>www.ucas.com</u></a></p><h2>POSTGRADUATE</h2><p>Applications are made direct to the School for the following taught postgraduate courses:</p><p><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=219" target="new window"><u>Diploma in Architecture</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=229" target="new window"><u>Master of Architecture</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=88" target="new window"><u>Master of Fine Art</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=182" target="new window"><u>Master of Design in 'Textiles as Fashion'</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=264" target="new window"><u>Master of Philosophy in 2D/3D Motion Graphics</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=313" target="new window"><u>Master of Philosophy in Art, Design and Architecture in Education</u></a></p><h2>RESEARCH DEGREES</h2><p>Applications are made direct to the School for the following research degrees:</p><p><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=1213" target="new window"><u>Master of Architecture by Dissertation</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=375" target="new window"><u>Master of Philosophy</u></a><br /><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=371" target="new window"><u>Doctor of Philosophy (PhD)</u></a></p><p>Members of staff from the School make regular visits overseas to make school visits, carry out joint research and attend exhibitions. In the coming months the following visits will be made:</p><p>31 March 2007, Education UK Exhibition, Tokyo<br />1 April 2007, Education UK Exhibition, Osaka.</p><p>If you would like to make an appointment to speak to us at one of these exhibitions please contact: international@gsa.ac.uk</p>
	

	

	

	

	

	

	
	
	
	
	


	
	







